The NSVS 14256825 Exoplanetary System


Overview

NSVS 14256825 is a star with 0.42 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.19 times its radius. It is located 2677.34 light years away from the solar system.

NSVS 14256825 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the NSVS 14256825 system


NSVS 14256825 b

NSVS 14256825 b was discovered by the Multiple Observatories observatory, in 2019-09, using the eclipse timing variations method. Its semi-major axis is 3.12 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of NSVS 14256825 b is 4499.700 times the mass of Earth. The radius of NSVS 14256825 b is 12.300 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, NSVS 14256825 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
